nge is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705210,"age":95,"year":"1600","julianDay":2305448,"title":"The Honourable East India Company","description":"The Honourable East India Company, a British joint-stock company, was established in 1600 for trade in the Indian Ocean region. At its height, the British East India Company had a private army which was twice the size of the British Army, ruled large sections of India, and revenues in the millions.","url":"https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofEngland/The-East-India-Company/","urlTitle":"Historic UK - The East India Company","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705212,"age":115,"year":"1620","julianDay":2312753,"title":"The Pilgrims Board the Mayflower","description":"\"The Pilgrims boarded the Mayflower in search of religious freedom in the New World in September 1620. The Mayflower set sail from Plymouth, England, with 102 passengers, 40 of whom called themselves \"\"Saints.\"\" After two stormy months at sea, the ship reached the New World. Nearly half of the group died during their first winter due to malnutrition and the harsh New England winter.\"","url":"https://www.themayflowersociety.org/the-pilgrims/pilgrim-history","urlTitle":"The Mayflower Society - Pilgrim History","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Mary was born in 1505, in England. She married Sir Anthony Cooke in 1520, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1505–":"1505–Surnud","1504–1576":"1504–1576","1525–1585":"1525–1585","1505–Female":"1505–Surnud","1525":"1525","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1600":"1600","1620":"1620","1576":"1576","1520":"1520","1585":"1585","1571":"1571","1505":"1505","1549":"1549","1504":"1504","Lyford, Berkshire, England":"Lyford, Berkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England"},"fi":{"1505–":"1505–Kuollut","1504–1576":"1504–1576","1525–1585":